## Quick Test

This is a simple test to verify PCM audio is working correctly.

```elixir
# Create recorder
test_recorder = KinoLiveAudio.new(
  chunk_size: 50,
  unit: :ms,
  sample_rate: 16_000
)

# Listen and parse PCM
test_recorder
|> Kino.listen(fn chunk ->
  # Parse Float32 samples
  samples = for <<sample::float-32-little <- chunk>>, do: sample

  # Verify format
  IO.puts("âœ… Received PCM chunk")
  IO.puts("   Bytes: #{byte_size(chunk)}")
  IO.puts("   Samples: #{length(samples)}")
  IO.puts("   First sample: #{List.first(samples)}")
  IO.puts("   Min: #{Enum.min(samples) |> Float.round(4)}")
  IO.puts("   Max: #{Enum.max(samples) |> Float.round(4)}")
  IO.puts("   ---")
end)

test_recorder
```

**Expected output when recording:**
```
